    "Id": "mechdef_kingcrabrauder_KCRD-X1",
    "Name": "King Crabrauder",
    "Details": "After launching a series of retaliatory raids against the Lyran Alliance as punishment for stealing the Light Engine plans from them, Wolfs Dragoons wound up finding a sizable cache of intact King Crab arms but without the corresponding torsos and legs. Unwilling to waste such a windfall, the Dragoon's kept them in storage in hopes of finding a use for them later. After the destruction of the Jihad, Wolfs Dragoons contracted Irian BattleMechs Unlimited to make use of those arms by attaching them to reworked Marauder II torsos and legs. The resulting mech was then fitted with extensive Clan-spec equipment to produce this unusual design. The 1B configuration is designed more for long range fire support, mounting twin Clan-spec Large Pulse Lasers and Inner Sphere grade Rotary Autocannon 5s in the arms. These heavy arm weapons are supported by twin LRM 15 launchers on the shoulders for additional fire support.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
    "Icon": "uixTxrIcon_crabshasapult"
  },
